games.summary: Jalen Johnson scored 22 points and had 13 rebounds, Nickeil Alexander-Walker scored 21 points, and the Atlanta Hawks beat Indiana 128-108 in NBA Cup group play on Friday night to keep the Pacers winless this season. Atlanta led 63-59 at halftime but outscored the Pacers 34-17 in the third.
blurbs: 📋 Nickeil Alexander-Walker (ATL) made just his 3rd start this season. 21 pts, 3 reb.

games.summary: Jaylen Brown scored 32 points, Anfernee Simons added 19 and the Boston Celtics never trailed in a 109-108 win against the Philadelphia 76ers on Friday night. Payton Pritchard and Derrick White had 15 points apiece for the Celtics, who evened their record at .500 by winning their third straight after beginning the season with three consecutive losses.

Jamison Battle scored 20 points, including a pair of 3-pointers that helped the Toronto Raptors pull away in the final two minutes of a 112-101 victory over the Cleveland Cavaliers in the NBA Cup opener for both teams Friday night. RJ Barrett and Brandon Ingram also scored 20 points apiece for the Raptors, who stopped a four-game losing streak that followed a season-opening win.
blurbs: 🆕 Dean Wade (CLE) made his first start of the season. 30 min, 5 pts.
📋 Jaylon Tyson (CLE) made just his 4th start this season. 18 pts, 3 reb.

games.summary: Josh Giddey scored a career-high 32 points with 10 rebounds and nine assists, Nikola Vucevic added 26 points, and the Chicago Bulls beat the New York Knicks 135-125 on Friday night to stay undefeated and get out to their best start in nearly three decades. Jalen Brunson scored 29 points and OG Anunoby had 26 to help power New York’s second-half comeback attempt.
MEMPHIS, Tenn. Austin Reaves added 21 points for the Lakers and Jake LaRavia scored 13.

Devin Booker scored 36 points and had nine assists to lead the Phoenix Suns to a 118-96 win over the Utah Jazz in NBA Cup group play on Friday night. Grayson Allen scored 14 points, Royce O'Neale and Ryan Dunn had 13 points each and Dunn grabbed 10 rebounds for the Suns, who snapped a four-game losing streak.
blurbs: 📋 Royce O'Neale (PHX) made just his 3rd start this season. 13 pts, 5 reb.

games.summary: PORTLAND, Ore. Jokic went into the game tied with Oscar Robertson (1961-62) and Russell Westbrook (2020-21) for most consecutive triple-doubles to start the season with four.
INGLEWOOD, Calif. scored 16 points, and Ivica Zubac had 14 points and 11 rebounds.
